<subSubSection lastPageId="36" lastPageNumber="37" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,1606,2029]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1606,1632]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Description</emphasis>
(
<specimenCount box="[352,373,1606,1632]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount box="[425,447,1607,1633]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
; not repeating characters common to 
<taxonomicName authority="Takano &amp; Gao &amp; Hu &amp; Li &amp; Yafuso &amp; Suwito &amp; Repin &amp; Pungga &amp; Meleng &amp; Kaliang &amp; Chong &amp; Toda, 2021" authorityName="Takano &amp; Gao &amp; Hu &amp; Li &amp; Yafuso &amp; Suwito &amp; Repin &amp; Pungga &amp; Meleng &amp; Kaliang &amp; Chong &amp; Toda" authorityYear="2021" box="[862,1033,1606,1633]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Colocasiomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kinabaluana" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[862,881,1607,1633]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[893,1033,1606,1632]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">kinabaluana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1039,1127,1606,1632]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1039,1127,1606,1632]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
). Head. Supracervical setae 5–8 per side, distally more or less curved, longer than inner occipital setae. Cibarial, medial sensilla 3–4 per side. Supralateral setae outside prementum 3–5 per side.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,1606,2029]" box="[199,882,1714,1741]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Thorax. Anterior dorsocentral setae behind transverse suture.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,1606,2029]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Abdomen. Male sternite III longer than wide, posteriorly slightly narrowing; IV wider than long (
<figureCitation box="[1317,1424,1750,1776]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="35.[151,250,1464,1488]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,183,1439]" captionTargetId="figure-18@35.[151,1435,181,1440]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 23. Colocasiomyia matthewsi Toda, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes). A, Male abdominal sternites (ventral view); B, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); C, periphallic organs (lateral view); D, phallic organs (lateral view); E, ditto (ventral view); F, female terminalia (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766452" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766452/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Fig. 23A</figureCitation>
). Female sternite V wider than long; VI wider than long, medially concaved on posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[1226,1329,1786,1812]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="35.[151,250,1464,1488]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,183,1439]" captionTargetId="figure-18@35.[151,1435,181,1440]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 23. Colocasiomyia matthewsi Toda, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes). A, Male abdominal sternites (ventral view); B, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); C, periphallic organs (lateral view); D, phallic organs (lateral view); E, ditto (ventral view); F, female terminalia (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766452" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766452/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Fig. 23B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,1606,2029]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Male terminalia. Cercus pubescent only on dorsal 2/5, with 56–57 setae, extended below, apically forming broad lobe marginally roundish and fringed with small setae (
<figureCitation box="[863,968,1858,1884]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="35.[151,250,1464,1488]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,183,1439]" captionTargetId="figure-18@35.[151,1435,181,1440]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 23. Colocasiomyia matthewsi Toda, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes). A, Male abdominal sternites (ventral view); B, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); C, periphallic organs (lateral view); D, phallic organs (lateral view); E, ditto (ventral view); F, female terminalia (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766452" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766452/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Fig. 23C</figureCitation>
). Phallapodeme sclerotized plate slightly oblique to phallal axis (
<figureCitation box="[415,519,1894,1920]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="35.[151,250,1464,1488]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,183,1439]" captionTargetId="figure-18@35.[151,1435,181,1440]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 23. Colocasiomyia matthewsi Toda, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes). A, Male abdominal sternites (ventral view); B, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); C, periphallic organs (lateral view); D, phallic organs (lateral view); E, ditto (ventral view); F, female terminalia (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766452" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766452/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Fig. 23D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,1606,2029]" box="[199,1147,1930,1957]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Female terminalia. Hypoproct medially with a small patch of pubescence (
<figureCitation box="[1034,1134,1930,1956]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="35.[151,250,1464,1488]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,183,1439]" captionTargetId="figure-18@35.[151,1435,181,1440]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 23. Colocasiomyia matthewsi Toda, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes). A, Male abdominal sternites (ventral view); B, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); C, periphallic organs (lateral view); D, phallic organs (lateral view); E, ditto (ventral view); F, female terminalia (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766452" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766452/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Fig. 23F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,1606,2029]" lastBlockId="36.[151,1437,150,717]" lastPageId="36" lastPageNumber="37" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Indices (range of 
<specimenCount box="[399,448,1966,1992]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="male">10♂</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount box="[505,554,1966,1992]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="female">10♀</specimenCount>
<typeStatus box="[562,675,1967,1993]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">paratypes</typeStatus>
): FW/HW = 0.53–0.58, ch/o = 0.28–0.36, prorb = 0.86–1.14, rcorb = 0.33–0.56, vb = 0.26–0.47, dcl = 0.57–0.74, sctl = 0.74–0.98, sterno = 0.65–1.10, orbito = 0.45–0.82, dcp = 0.97–1.30, sctlp = 1.27–1.82, C = 1.74–2.12, 4c = 0.92–1.08, 4v = 1.42–1.60, 5x = 0.72–1.14, ac = 2.60–3.45, M = 0.28–0.40.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
